reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The BEES KNEES!
reviews.reviewText: These are like meatballs to my pasta! Like bananas to a monkey! Cheese to my macaroni and the bees to my honey!Speaking of honey... hunneee... let me just tell YOU! They charge like nobody's business. Except mine. It's my business to charge them but it's so fast. Like Flash... only maybe one less motion than Flash. Not like Green Lantern at all... because let's be honest, nobody liked the Green Lantern movie. Even when we all love Ryan Reynolds, we all agree ... he should have left this one out.Back to the headphones, did I mention the soft feel of them? Better than a new baby's bottom... and no dirty diapers to change either. The silicone feel outside makes them easy to slip in my delightful ears and get ready to rock. Or roll. I like to be all inclusive.Sounds are amazing! I'd say Madison Square Garden only in your livingroom, while you enjoy it from the peace of your own quarantined home until we all can go back to normal. These are the next beat thing.Now, go get you some. Buy 2 they're small. And let's be honest, someone you know is going to say "OMG! Can I borrow those?" And you know it's like when you used to loan your DVDS or your best sweatshirt... ya not gettin' back.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have had these for almost a year now and they've worked great the whole time. I bought them for running so I've sweat all over them repeatedly and haven't had an issue. I'm not super picky about sound quality but I have no issues with the sound quality and the volume is good too. And they actually fit & stay in my ears. A lot of others don't; I have small ears & tragus piercings so it can be difficult to find ear buds that fit. They last a long time and charge quickly and the little charging case is very handy.My only complaint is that I'd like some warning as to when they need to be charged, and maybe there is something, but I can't figure it out. I find the charging system a little confusing. They've died on me in the middle of a run before which was unfortunate. But still, I'm very happy with these - and their longevity - so far!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Sounds ok. Can't charge w/ the ear bands on. No signal 20ft from phone. Microphone doesn't work.
reviews.reviewText: Quality is ok, I used Planet Fitness basic wired earbuds prior to this & I'd say quality is a little better than those. They don't have a very bassy or high treble sound, but still pretty good. I tried a sound equalizer app which made a slight difference but not enough to keep on my phone. Spotify has it's own equalizer in settings so I played with that & it helped enough to satisfy me as far as sound is concerned.What also helps, is putting on the (don't know what else to call them but) ear snugger rubber bands that go around the outside of the fat mid-inner ear plastic part. This also creates an extra comfortable sound barrier & helps to keep them snugly in place during activities.I love that they have the ear hook on them, that's the biggest reason besides price that I bought these.The big downside, which may cause me to return these, is that although I'd love to wear the rubber ear snug bands each time I use these because it makes them more comfy, helps with sound quality & noise cancelling, you have to take the bands on and off before each time you charge or store the ear buds.They won't plop into the charger with the bands on. You can't even squeeze them in. It's such a silly thing, I wish they'd made the charging ports just 1 millimeter bigger for that purpose. So you have to take off the bands each time you charge or put them in their box for any reason, which eventually will destroy the bands, all that stretching etc. Plus the inconvenience.I have pics to show what I mean. The first pic shows the buds in the charger without the bands on them. I'm holding up the band I'm talking about. Second pic shows them with the bands on. You can't even push them in there.I love the color, so that's another plus. Battery life seems great.However the microphone hasn't worked for me yet during phone calls, so that's another bummer. My friends can't hear me on the other end, they say it just sounds like static. So we will see.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best affordable headphones I’ve tried!
reviews.reviewText: Sound quality is amazing. Literally sounds like they are in the room with me right off the bat. Doesn’t need to be “broken in” to sound good.***COMFORT WISE THOUGH these are the BEST headphones I have worn out of the many cheap-side Amazon headphones I have bought through the years. My dog has an unfortunate, bad habit of chewing headphones if we leave them sitting out, so I’ve tried the Jlab over ear hook, Occiam, Bmani, just to name my most recent ones.Of all the ones I’ve had these are my favorite fit and comfort by far!! I have smaller ears so others sometimes fit loose and feel clunky. I also like the jlabs fit, but I prefer the push button on these, I would always hit the jlabs tap controls by accident while adjusting or something.The noise cancellation is VERY effective. No option of turning that on or off but it is super effective especially at such a low price point. I will probably use them single earpiece at a time majority of the time so I can still hear what’s going on in the house. But I do love to melt away and not hear my surroundings so that’s a big plus that it has good noise cancellation.I will do my very best to keep these away from my dog for sure!!*1 year later- these are still my favorite! Sound quality trumps every pair I’ve tried from affordable brands

Estos audifonos los compre para mi esposa, dado a que sus rutinas de ejercicio son fuertes, casi todos lo otros audifonos se le salian por completo de la oreja, pero estos no, la patita para detenerse es muy util y su flexibilidad hace que no te de molestia o te canse. Ademas el audio suena super bien, supero mi espectativa. El precio esta acorde a la calidad y la duracion de la pila es muy buena, pero supongo que es porque estan nuevos.

reviews.reviewTitle: Sehr angenehm zu tragen, gute Qualität
reviews.reviewText: Qualität und Preis top, gute Passform, weiches Material, gut für Sport und Brillenträger. Nach vielen Versuchen, endlich das passende gefunden.

Der rechte Ohrhörer funktionierte nach 6 Monaten nicht mehr, trotz mehrfacher Kopplungsversuche laut Handbuch. Ich kann das Produkt nicht empfehlen. Meine billigen Hörer aus dem Drogeriemarkt funktionieren wesentlich besser.
No o tiene ni calidad material ni sonora

reviews.reviewTitle: Mala calidad de sonido pero son cómodos.
reviews.reviewText: Son cómodos para llevarlos haciendo ejercicio, sin embargo la calidad de sonido es muy mala, graves desproporcionados y medios y agudos desastrosos, por lo que cuestan hay mejores opciones. Otro punto muy negativo es que los controles son de botón, no reaccionan al tacto como otros modelos, por lo que para manejarlos hay que apretar el botón, lo que hace que se metan dentro del oido de una forma muy molesta. No los recomendaria.
